Name: ductal carcinoma in situ
Definition: A breast carcinoma in situ that is characterized by being non-invasive

Name: lobular neoplasia
Definition: A breast carcinoma in situ that is characterized by abnormal cells are found in the lobules (glands that make milk) of the breast.

Name: breast apocrine carcinoma in situ
Definition: A breast carcinoma in situ that is characterized by abundant eosinophilic apocrine cytoplasm and large nuclei. It is a variant of ductal carcinoma in situ of the breast.
Synonym: Apocrine carcinoma in situ of the breast

Name: obsolete testicular seminoma with syncytiotrophoblastic cells
Definition: A breast carcinoma in situ that is characterized by abundant eosinophilic apocrine cytoplasm and large nuclei. It is a variant of ductal carcinoma in situ of the breast.
Synonym: Apocrine carcinoma in situ of the breast
